ndividuals with  have often been described as having a wide-based or ataxic-like gait, and a smiling, happy and sociable personality. his, combined with absent speech, microcephaly and seizures, has led some individuals to be given a presumptive diagnosis of ngelman syndrome [19]. owever, the facial features of , in addition to the other typical congenital anomalies, distinguish these two conditions.
